  "report_text": "# Governance and Source Policy\n\nPublic protocol and tool-use materials show permissions, safety boundaries, and policy enforcement as explicit system concerns.[1][2]\n\nThe same materials also surface a real comparison tension: governance is clearly first-class, but the exact split between protocol-level permissions and product-specific safety overlays remains uncertain enough that reviewer-facing reports should state that ambiguity explicitly.[1][2]\n",
